Alhaji Adisa Logun, the Chief of Staff to the Kwara State Governor, is dead. This was confirmed in a twitter post by the Special Assistant, New Media to Kwara State Governor, Fafoluyi Olayinka. He said, “Kwara State Chief Of Staff, Aminu Adisa Logun Is Dead.. Indeed, death is the next thing after birth. Black Tuesday here in Kwara.” The late Aminu Adisa logun was appointed the Chief of Staff of kwara State Governor in 2019, few weeks after swearing-in of Gov. Abdulrahman Abdulrazaq. Details shortly… The Nation By Olayinka Owolewa Ilorin - No fewer than 3,040 athletes from across the country have converged on Ilorin to participate at the 20th edition of Nigeria polytechnics games (NIPOGA) holding at the Kwara capital from Feb. 5 to Feb. 16. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), reports that the biannual… February 8, 2020 In "Sports" By Abiodun Esan Ilorin - Gov. AbulRahman AbdulRazaq of Kwara has declared that he busied himself with fixing of decayed infrastructure in the state during the first 100 days of his administration. AbdulRazaq made this known on Thursday in Ilorin while addressing newsmen on the occasion of his 100 days… September 5, 2019 In "News" IBADAN (Sundiata Post) - Oyo State Governor, Mr. Seyi Makinde has confirmed the appointment of the Group Politics Editor of Tribune Newspapers, Mr. Taiwo Adisa as his Chief Press Secretary. The appointment, which takes immediate effect, was confirmed in a statement made available to journalists in Ibadan by the Chief… June 3, 2019 In "Top Stories"